  "short_text": "Factorial Calculation",
  "content": "Complete the  function to calculate the factorial of a given number using built-in function.\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe **`calculate_factorial`** function takes one parameter: a single integer `n` as input.\n\n\n---\n\n#### Output\nThe  **`calculate_factorial`** should return an integer representing the factorial of `n`.\n\n---\n\n\n#### Explanation\n\nThe factorial of a number `n` is the product of all positive integers less than or equal to `n`. For example, factorial(5) = **5 x 4 x 3 x 2 x 1 = 120**.",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
